ICAP Says Foreign-Exchange Trading Rises, Treasury Volume Drops

-- B y   A n c h a l e e   W o r r a c h a t e
-- 
2011-10-05T12:49:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-05/icap-says-foreign-exchange-trading-rises-treasury-volume-drops.html
ICAP Plc (IAP) , the worldâ€™s largest broker
of transactions between banks, said the total volume of
electronic trading going through its two major platforms rose 14
percent in September from a year earlier to $856.7 billion.  The average amount of daily spot currency trading on its
EBS platform climbed 25 percent from the previous year to $183.1
billion. Trading of U.S. Treasuries on its BrokerTec platform
fell 12 percent in the same period, the company said in an e-
mailed statement.  Fixed-income products trading through the BrokerTec
platform increased 11 percent on the year to $673.5 billion a
day, the company said.  To contact the reporter responsible for this story:
